text: Camano Island is a large island in Possession Sound, a section of Puget Sound. It is part of Island County, Washington, and is located between Whidbey Island and the mainland (Snohomish County). The island has a total area of , making it one of the largest in the state of Washington. It has a year-round population of 17,356 as of the 2020 census. It is an unincorporated area with several small communities. Camano Island is home to two state parks, Cama Beach and Camano Island State Park, and several county and local parks. ==References== Category:Islands of the United States Category:Census- designated places in Washington (state) Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
